[Event "Vienna repertoire: Gambit main line"]
[Site "OpenChessTrainer"]
[Result "*"]

{ 2.Nc3 then 3.f4: a King's Gambit where Black cannot safely accept.
The main line 3...d5 is Black's best - know it well from both sides. }
1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 d5 { The right answer - everything else
favours White quickly. } 4. fxe5 Nxe4 5. Nf3 Be7 (5... Nxc3 6. bxc3
{ The recapture opens the b-file and builds a big centre with d4. }
6... Be7 7. d4 O-O 8. Bd3) 6. d4 O-O 7. Bd3 f5 8. exf6 { En passant,
before ...f5 fixes the centre in Black's favour. } 8... Nxf6 9. O-O *

[Event "Vienna repertoire: vs 2...Nc6"]
[Site "OpenChessTrainer"]
[Result "*"]

{ Without ...Nf6 there is no ...d5 counter: develop with Bc4, delay f4
until it comes with full force. }
1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 (3... Bc5 4. Qg4 { The famous problem
move: g7 is attacked and 4...Qf6?? 5.Nd5! wins material. } 4... g6
5. Qf3 { Re-aim at f7; Black's dark squares are already loose. } 5...
Nf6 6. Nge2) 4. d3 Bc5 5. f4 d6 6. Nf3 O-O 7. Na4 { With f4 played the c5 bishop
stares at g1: castling is illegal until it is gone. Trade it off
first. } 7... Bb6 8. Nxb6 axb6 9. O-O Na5 10. Bb3 Nxb3 11. axb3 c6
12. Qe1 { The classic lift: Qh4, f5 and Ng5 aim at the king. } *

[Event "Vienna repertoire: vs 2...Bc5"]
[Site "OpenChessTrainer"]
[Result "*"]

{ 2...Bc5 ignores the centre. Take it with d4 at the right moment and
develop with tempo on the exposed bishop. }
1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Bc5 3. Nf3 d6 (3... Nc6 4. Bc4 Nf6 5. d3 d6 6. O-O
{ A pleasant Italian where f4 is still coming as a plan. }) 4. d4
exd4 5. Nxd4 Nf6 6. Be2 O-O 7. O-O Re8 8. Bg5 { The pin is annoying
now that ...Be7 costs a tempo. } 8... h6 9. Bh4 *
